VIPex Parcel Service System – Full Structure
System Overview

VIPex Parcel Service System is a digital logistics and parcel management platform designed to help customers send parcels easily while allowing staff, riders, and management to handle deliveries efficiently across multiple branches.

The system improves parcel tracking, delivery speed, payment management, customer satisfaction, and business operations.

User Types and Their Functions
1. Customer

The customer uses the system to:

Register and log in
Create parcel delivery requests
Enter sender details
Enter receiver details
Choose delivery type (Standard / Express / Same-Day)
View delivery price automatically
Make payments
Track parcel using tracking number or QR code
View parcel delivery status
Receive SMS / Email / WhatsApp notifications
View delivery history
Contact customer support
Rate delivery service
View proof of delivery
2. Admin (Super Admin)

The admin manages the entire system and can:

Manage customers
Manage staff accounts
Manage riders/couriers
Manage branch managers
Add / Edit / Delete branches
View all parcel records
Assign parcels to delivery staff
Monitor all deliveries
Approve or reject delivery requests
Set delivery pricing rules
Manage service zones
View payment records
Generate reports
View business analytics
Manage complaints
Manage system settings
Manage security and permissions
3. Delivery Staff / Courier Rider

The rider handles parcel delivery and can:

Log in securely
View assigned deliveries
Accept delivery tasks
Confirm parcel pickup
Update parcel status:
Picked Up
In Transit
Arrived at Branch
Out for Delivery
Delivered
Failed Delivery
Upload proof of delivery (photo / signature)
Report delivery issues
View delivery routes
View delivery schedule
Receive dispatch notifications
4. Branch Staff / Branch Manager

Branch staff manages branch operations and can:

Register parcels received at branch
Verify sender and receiver details
Confirm parcel arrival
Confirm parcel departure
Update parcel movement between branches
Manage branch delivery records
Handle customer complaints
Assist customers with parcel tracking
Verify payments at branch
Generate branch reports
Monitor branch performance
5. Accountant / Finance Officer (Optional)

The accountant handles financial operations and can:

View all payment transactions
Verify successful payments
Manage delivery revenue
Generate financial reports
Track rider payouts
Handle customer refunds
Monitor branch income
Manage invoices
View profit/loss reports